Appendix D: Convex Geometry of Correlations and NPA Hierarchy

D.1 Correlation Sets

Define $\mathcal{C}_{\text{class}}$, $\mathcal{C}_{\text{quant}}$, $\mathcal{C}_{\text{NS}}$ as in Chapter 4.

D.2 NPA Hierarchy

Definition D.1. For a bipartite scenario with measurement settings $x\in X$, $y\in Y$ and outcomes $a\in A$, $b\in B$, define moment matrix $\Gamma$ with rows/columns indexed by words in measurement operators. The $k$-th level of the NPA hierarchy imposes positivity of $\Gamma$ truncated to words of length $\le k$, plus linear constraints from probability normalization and no-signalling. This yields a sequence of SDP outer approximations converging to $\mathcal{C}_{\text{quant}}$.

Theorem D.2. $\mathcal{C}_{\text{quant}}^{(k)}$ is described by an SDP of size $O((|X||A|+|Y||B|)^k)$. As $k\to\infty$, $\mathcal{C}_{\text{quant}}^{(k)} \searrow \mathcal{C}_{\text{quant}}$.

D.3 Semidefinite Programming Formulation

For level 1 (the "commuting" level), the SDP is:
\max \sum_{abxy} \beta_{abxy} \operatorname{Tr}(\rho E_{a|x} \otimes F_{b|y})


subject to $\rho \ge 0$, $\operatorname{Tr}(\rho)=1$, $\{E_{a|x}\}$ and $\{F_{b|y}\}$ projection-valued measures. This is bilinear, hence non-convex; but the NPA hierarchy linearizes by treating $\rho$ and measurements implicitly via moment matrix.

D.4 Sum-of-Squares Relaxations

For non-commutative polynomial optimization, the ncSoS relaxation of level $k$ is the SDP:
\max \langle \beta, \Gamma \rangle


s.t. $\Gamma \succeq 0$, $\Gamma_{1,1}=1$, $\Gamma$ satisfies moment constraints from $*$-algebra relations.

